    "We did not find strong signals of interventions to increase growth for this specific category of tools.",
    "3 There are no obvious technical barriers to rapid scaling.",
    "Multiple data types are important for the diverse tools in this category, some of which are costly to generate, but the highest-risk tools use sequence data sampled over a period of time.",
    "There is already a large volume of historical pathogen sequence data and the rate of data generation is increasing rapidly as costs decline and genomic biosurveillance becomes more widespread globally.",
    "One tool gave accurate predictions for immune escape of multiple pandemic potential viruses when trained on corresponding data, and if suitable data exists for other concerning pathogens then it is likely that this approach will also work for them."
